    788          /**
    789           *    @brief    This method performs volatile memory (CPU register, Stack) test periodically.
    790           *    @details  This method is responsible for:
    791           *              CPU Registers Test,
    792           *              Stack memory complete test
    793           *              Stack overflow and underflow test.
    794           *
    795           *              MICRO_NUM_BYTE_FOR_RAM_CONTINUOUS_TEST configuration macro defined in the SRMicro_prv.h file
    796           *              Defines how many bytes will be processed during each interaction of the Continuous stack memory Test.
    797           *
    798           *
    799           *              The time taken for complete stack memory test is calculated below-
    800           *              FULL RAM TEST (in ms) = (Stack Size/ MICRO_NUM_BYTE_FOR_RAM_CONTINUOUS_TEST) *
    801           *                                       Call rate(of Micro__RamTest())
    802           *
    803           *             For example-
    804           *              Stack memory  size is 2048bytes,  number of bytes processed in each call are 4 and the call rate is 100ms then,
    805           *              FULL  Stack memory(in ms) =  (2048/4)*100 ms
    806           *                                        =  51200 ms
    807           *
    808           *              Along with this it provides the flow control log and exception control for each tests.
    809           *
    810           *              This API is been called from ApplienceMgr Thread at every 100ms
    811           */
    812          #pragma optimize=none

